The annual report shall include:
a summary description of the system that includes the pipeline facility;
a description of the product transported in the pipeline facility and system;
State and local emergency response liaison information;
a description of the leak detection system in use for the pipeline facility;
a description of periodic testing methods used on the pipeline facility and a summary of results of the testing; and
any other information that the Commission requires.

At least once every 5 years, an intrastate pipeline operator shall:
identify each owner of real property on which the pipeline facility is located;
notify each property owner of the presence of the pipeline facility on the owner's property;
verify that each property owner has received the notice; and
provide to the Commission a current list of all property owners.
